passages.text: August 28, 2025 07:59 AM GMT

VNET has received invitations to new datacenter procurement from more than 1 customer and is under negotiations with potential closing in September. The company has set a preliminary target of 400MW capacity delivery in 2026 implying 300- 400MW order wins in the next 12 months. No orders in 2Q25 was a result of financial constraints as more capacity delivery in 2025 could further increase its leverage ratio. New project IRR reached mid- teens levels due to faster ramp up from customers and shortened testing period while MSR is largely stable. Supply side also remains disciplined with no incremental datacenter projects approved after the window guidance from the government.

With the shares trading at 10x 2026E EV/EBITDA, we remain Ow as we see more upside potential coming from: 1) potential new orders from the tendering as well as the 66MW order renegotiation, and 2) guidance revision if ramp up remains intact.
